result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Quintin Dominic Jones

records.addlTxt: Letter from defendant re:  bail reduction.  (Quintin D. Jones - #2022008477, Milwaukee County Jail, 949 N 9th St, Milwaukee WI 53233).

Defendant Quintin Dominic Jones not in court, in custody.  Attorney Michael J Cerniglia appeared by video for Quintin Dominic Jones.  Attorney Mallory R Davis appeared by video for State of Wisconsin. 
Status conference held. Defense requests Final Pretrial and Jury Trial dates. State placed final offer on the record. Defendant rejected offer. State withdrew their offer to the defendant.  Any witness lists, special jury instructions, and motion in limine to be filed 48 hours before the final pretrial date. Court orders case adjourned for final pretrial and jury trial in Branch 29.
Final pre-trial scheduled for November 10, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Jury trial scheduled for December 12, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Quintin Dominic Jones not in court, in custody.  Attorney Michael J Cerniglia appeared by video for Quintin Dominic Jones.  Prosecuting attorney Katherine Seelow appeared on behalf of Mallory Davis by video for the State of Wisconsin. Case in court for Scheduling Conference. Defendant not produced. Discovery issues put forth on the record. Case adjourned for a Status Conference to Br 29.
Status conference scheduled for September 30, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

CASE HEARD IN PRELIM FOR BR. 29:
Defendant Quintin Dominic Jones in court with Attorney Michael J Cerniglia; both appear by video.  Defendant Quintin Dominic Jones in custody.  Katrina Amy Voge appeared in person for the State of Wisconsin.  
Court took judicial notice of 08CF6144. Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the State: West Allis Officer J. Cooper. State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Branch 29.  Scheduling conference scheduled for August 30, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Court ordered no contact with KNE (DOB 12/9/96); KLJ (DOB 10/21/21); KNJ (DOB 8/19/20); JJO (DOB 9/16/81)
No Contact/No Weapons Order, signed and filed.
Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 3.  No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Quintin Dominic Jones in court with attorney Michael J Cerniglia.  Defendant Quintin Dominic Jones in custody.  Nate Kristian McClure appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Kiefer Branch 29.  Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold the defendant for further proceedings.  Court advised defendant that due to nature of offense a sample of your DNA is required.  If the sheriff's department hasn't already obtained a sample I order them to do so.  There are circumstances that you can request the sample to be expunged from the data base pursuant to statute 165.77(4). DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  Case is adjourned for preliminary hearing in Branch PE.
  This hearing will be streamed live on Dacast:  https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/99073afd-37c2-acfa-830d-b1ddcaebf0ea  Preliminary hearing scheduled for July 20, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
